-- Edwards Wildman Palmer Law Firm Names Robert Shuftan as Managing Partner
-- B y   S o p h i a   P e a r s o n
-- 2012-01-31T21:30:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-31/edwards-wildman-palmer-law-firm-names-robert-shuftan-as-managing-partner.html
Edwards Wildman Palmer LLP (1290L) , the 650-
attorney U.S.  law firm , named Robert Shuftan as its new managing
partner.  Shuftan’s appointment will take effect Feb. 2, the firm
said today in a  statement . Edwards Wildman also elected Laurence
Harris to serve as deputy managing partner and Alan Levin as
firm chairman, according to the statement. All three will serve
three-year terms, the firm said.  “This is an exciting opportunity to lead an excellent law
firm with broad practices and geography, strong clients and very
talented lawyers,” Shuftan said in the statement. “We are
confident that the firm is poised for additional growth and
success.”  Shuftan, based in Chicago, served as managing partner of
Wildman Harrold Allen & Dixon LLP for 13 years before that firm
merged in October with Edwards Angell Palmer & Dodge to form the
current firm. He succeeds Walter Reed, who will resume regular
practice.  Edwards Wildman has offices in the U.S., U.K. and  Japan .
The firm also has an associated office in Hong Kong.  To contact the reporter on this story:
